Many people had never heard of Amber Heard before they read gossip about her marriage to Elon Musk and her messy divorce from Johnny Depp. Although she has starred in small roles, Aquaman has been a major role in her career.  “Amber Heard '' Career on BIG Downfall & Loss To Johnny Depp. Her career has taken a bad turn since the allegations of domestic violence against her. Let's take a look inside Amber Heard and learn more about her past. 

Amber Laura Heard, an American actress in television and film, was born April 22, 1986. She learned to ride horses before moving to Los Angeles from Austin, Texas to be a model and an actress.  “Amber Heard '' Career on BIG Downfall & Loss To Johnny Depp. Her dad used to take her on fishing and hunting trips. As a child, she was a beauty queen. She was raised in a conservative household and dropped out of school at 17 to follow her dreams. 

Before landing her first major role in the horror film All The Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), she had landed a few roles. Her first mainstream roles were in Never Back Down's action movie (2008) and the comedy Pineapple Express (2008). She was in a relationship with Tasya VanRee, an American painter and photographer. 

It is interesting to see that Amber's marriage to Johnny Depp wasn't the only one that had domestic disputes and rumored violence.  “Amber Heard” Career on BIG Downfall & Loss To Johnny Depp. 

Heard was still in a relationship with Tasya VanRee in 2009 when he was arrested at the Seattle airport. Heard and Tasya got into a fight, which resulted in Tasya striking Heard. Heard was eventually sent home with a fourth-degree misdemeanor assault (domestic violence) charge. The Seattle Police received a request in 2011 to remove the arrest information from the case. This was allowed by Washington State Law.
